UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1025
1 AN ACT relating to unemployment insurance.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 Section 1. KRS 341.005 is amended to read as follows:
4 As used in this chapter, unless the context clearly requires otherwise:
5 (1) "Approved job training or certification program" means:
6 (a) A program approved by the secretary that leads to a short-term certificate or
7 credential, an industry-recognized certificate, diploma, or associate of applied
8 science degree in one (1) of Kentucky's top five (5) high-demand workforce
9 sectors identified by the Kentucky Workforce Innovation Board and the
10 Education and Labor Cabinet;
11 (b) A program approved and determined by the secretary to improve an
12 individual's employability in a high-wage, high-demand occupation; or
13 (c) A training program approved under the Trade Act of 1974, 19 U.S.C. sec.
14 2296;
15 (2) "Cabinet" means the Education and Labor Cabinet;
16 (3) "Certified mail" has the same meaning as in KRS 446.010;
17 (4) "Commission" means the Unemployment Insurance Commission;
18 (5)[(4)] "Enhanced federal benefits" means any temporary federally funded or
19 partially federally funded benefits, administered by the Commonwealth and payable
20 through voluntary agreements between the Commonwealth and the United States
21 Department of Labor, that supplement or increase weekly state benefit amounts.
22 "Enhanced federal benefits" does not mean benefits such as, without limitation,
23 benefits otherwise calculated and distributed in accordance with KRS 341.350 to
24 341.415, extended benefits provided for in KRS 341.700 to 341.740, shared work
25 benefits provided for in KRS 341.4161 to 341.4173, disaster unemployment
26 assistance benefits, 42 U.S.C. sec. 5177, or trade readjustment allowances, 19
27 U.S.C. secs. 2291 to 2294, or any amendments thereto;
