1 (6)[(5)] "Multi-factor authentication" means authentication through verification of
2 at least two (2) of the following methods of authentication factors:
3 1. Knowledge factors, such as a password;
4 2. Possession factors, such as a token or text message on a mobile phone; or
5 3. Inherence factors, such as a biometric characteristic;
6 (7) "Notice" means any communication from the secretary or any employer to
7 employers or employees required under this chapter;
8 (8) "Secretary" means the secretary of the Education and Labor Cabinet or his or her
9 duly authorized representative; and
10 (9)[(6)] "State average unemployment rate" means the seasonal adjusted statewide
11 unemployment rate that applies to the six (6) month period in which the claim is
12 filed. One six (6) month period shall begin on January 1 of each year and one six
13 (6) month period shall begin on July 1 of each year. For the six (6) month period
14 beginning on January 1, the state average unemployment rate shall be the average
15 of Kentucky's seasonal adjusted unemployment rates for the preceding months of
16 July, August, and September. For the six (6) month period beginning on July 1, the
17 state average unemployment rate shall be the average of Kentucky's seasonal
18 adjusted unemployment rates for the preceding months of January, February, and
19 March. In calculating the state average unemployment rate, the cabinet shall utilize
20 the most recent seasonal adjusted unemployment rate determined by the United
21 States Department of Labor, Bureau of Labor Statistics.
22 SECTION 2. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 341 IS CREATED TO
23 READ AS FOLLOWS:
24 Unless otherwise provided by law, any notice from the secretary or any employer to
25 employers or employees required under this chapter shall be in writing and delivered
26 by any method of governmental, commercial, or electronic delivery. The secretary shall
27 provide employers and employees the option to receive only electronic notices. The
